But the council decided to push ahead with the sale and Old Flo is now destined for a Christie’s sale in February.

It is believed the sculpture could fetch up to £20million after Henry Moore's Reclining Figure: Festival, built in 1951, sold for £19.1million in February despite being estimated as being worth £3.5 million to £4.5 million.

But a similar sculpture of a Draped Reclining Woman sold for significantly less in 2008 for £4.3million.

Moore is still considered one of Britain's best sculptures and was a trustee of both the National Gallery and Tate Gallery.

